cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.DB, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a recurrent neural network model for time series data in electronic health records. The focus is on predicting clinical outcomes based on physiological parameters, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses missing data, which could be relevant to database (cs.DB) and computational epidemiology (cs.CE). Finally, the use of a neural network model suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
